      "modelAnswer": "Formula: ACV (%) = Weight passing 2.36 mm / Weight of sample × 100\n\n= 374 / 2200 × 100\n= 17.0%\n\nAssessment:\n- ACV ≤ 30%: Generally acceptable for structural concrete.\n- ACV ≤ 10%: Excellent (very hard aggregate like granite/basalt).\n- ACV > 45%: Not suitable for concrete.\n\nAt ACV = 17%, this aggregate is GOOD and suitable for structural concrete including medium to high-strength grades. Two trials must be run and the average reported; if the two results differ by more than 0.5%, the test should be repeated."
