      "modelAnswer": "(i) Residue on 45 micron sieve = B / A × 100\n= 62 / 200 × 100\n= 31.0%\n\n(ii) IS 3812 Part 1 limit for residue on 45 micron sieve = 34% (maximum).\n\nAt 31%, this fly ash is within the limit and ACCEPTABLE as per IS 3812 Part 1.\n\nPractical note: Just because it meets the IS limit does not mean it will perform consistently. If a previous lot had only 15% residue (finer fly ash) and this lot has 31% (coarser), the fresh concrete properties (flowability, water demand) will differ. RDC practice is to set plant-specific tighter limits to maintain consistency in concrete production."
