      "modelAnswer": "(i) Water Reduction (%) = (Control water – Admixture water) / Control water × 100\n= (210 – 163) / 210 × 100\n= 47 / 210 × 100\n= 22.38%\n\nAt 22.38%, this qualifies as a High-Range Water Reducer (HRWR / Superplasticizer) — well above the 12% minimum for ASTM Type F classification.\n\n(ii) Admixture weight:\nCementitious content = 320 + 80 = 400 kg\nAdmixture weight = 0.8% × 400 = 0.008 × 400 = 3.2 kg\n\nSo 3.2 kg of admixture was added to achieve this water reduction."
