      "modelAnswer": "Correct Answer: (a) Only Statement 1 is correct.\n\nStatement 1 is CORRECT. IS 2386 is the multi-part Indian Standard for \"Methods of Test for Aggregates for Concrete\":\n- Part 1: Particle size and shape (sieve analysis, material finer than 75 micron, flakiness, elongation)\n- Part 3: Specific gravity and water absorption\n- Part 4: Mechanical properties (ACV, AIV)\n- Part 3 also covers bulk density.\nAll test methods referenced in the Kaushal Technical course fall under IS 2386.\n\nStatement 2 is WRONG — the two standards are described in reverse. The correct relationship is:\n- IS 2386 = TEST METHODS (how to test)\n- IS 383:2016 = SPECIFICATION / REQUIREMENTS (what the aggregate must comply with — grading limits, permissible values, etc.)\nBoth standards must be used together for a complete aggregate quality assurance programme."
