      "modelAnswer": "Role of the QC team:\nThe QC team is responsible for ensuring that all raw materials entering the plant meet approved specifications before they are used in concrete production. This includes:\n- Receiving and sampling new material lots.\n- Conducting tests as per the Inspection and Test Plan (ITP).\n- Comparing results against approved limits (IS standards + RDC internal specs).\n- Accepting, rejecting, or quarantining non-conforming material.\n- Maintaining records for traceability in case of complaints.\n\nWhy sales and finance should understand these tests:\n\nFor Sales:\n- When a customer raises a complaint about concrete quality, the salesperson is the first point of contact. Basic knowledge of tests like moisture content, ACV, silt content helps them ask the right questions and explain the investigation process credibly — building trust.\n- Understanding why certain materials cost more (e.g., low ACV granite vs. local stone) helps justify pricing to customers.\n- The Kaushal program prepares sales staff to handle first-level technical queries independently.\n\nFor Finance:\n- Raw material quality directly affects costs — high-silt sand increases water and cement demand; poor admixture lots need higher doses. Understanding tests helps finance team correlate raw material costs with production efficiency.\n- Budgeting for lab equipment, testing frequency, and qualified lab staff requires understanding what tests are critical."
