      "modelAnswer": "Correct Answer: (c) Both are correct.\n\nStatement 1 is CORRECT. IS 2386 (Parts 1–4) provides the step-by-step test methods for aggregate properties — how to measure them. IS 383:2016 is the specification standard that tells you what values are acceptable — grading zones, permissible limits for fines, ACV limits etc. Both must be used together: IS 2386 to conduct the test; IS 383:2016 to decide if the result is acceptable.\n\nStatement 2 is CORRECT. IS 9103 is the Indian Standard for admixtures for concrete. It covers:\n- Classification of admixtures (water reducers, retarders, accelerators, etc.)\n- Performance requirements (minimum water reduction, setting time limits, etc.)\n- Test methods including the water reduction test procedure.\nIt is the primary reference standard for admixture procurement and quality monitoring in Indian RMC plants."
