      "modelAnswer": "When a new lot of admixture arrives, it must not simply be accepted based on the supplier's test certificate. The plant should verify performance against the approved MASTER sample (the original approved batch).\n\nProcedure:\n1. Prepare TWO trial concrete mixes simultaneously, using exactly the same materials, sources, and proportions:\n - Mix 1: Using Master (approved) admixture\n - Mix 2: Using incoming new lot admixture\n\n2. Add the same admixture dose to both mixes. Record the initial slump of both mixes.\n\n3. Check SLUMP RETENTION: Measure slump of both mixes every 30 minutes (at 30 min, 60 min, 90 min if needed). Compare how slump drops over time in both mixes.\n\nTwo key properties checked:\n1. WATER REDUCTION: Does the new lot reduce water by the same % as the master sample to achieve the target slump?\n2. SLUMP RETENTION: Does the new lot maintain workability for long enough (important for sites far from the plant)?\n\nIf new lot shows lower water reduction or faster slump loss compared to master: increase admixture dose or inform supplier. If significantly worse, reject the lot and document the non-conformance."
