      "modelAnswer": "(i) Free surface moisture = Moisture content – Water absorption\n= 6.0% – 1.5% = 4.5%\n\n(ii) The sand has 4.5% free surface water — it will CONTRIBUTE this water to the mix.\n\nExtra water from sand = 4.5% × 750 = 0.045 × 750 = 33.75 kg of free water\n\nCorrections:\n- Batching water must be REDUCED: 165 – 33.75 = 131.25 kg ≈ 131 kg\n- Sand batch weight must be INCREASED to account for the extra water weight it carries:\n Sand to batch = 750 + 33.75 = 783.75 kg ≈ 784 kg\n (We batch more sand so that after subtracting water, the dry sand weight is still 750 kg)\n\nThis correction ensures that the effective w/c ratio and dry aggregate quantity remain exactly as per mix design, maintaining the designed strength."
