      "modelAnswer": "Eight aggregate tests covered in the Kaushal Technical Course:\n\n1. Moisture Content Test — measures how much water is present on/in the aggregate as a % of its dry weight.\n\n2. Specific Gravity & Water Absorption — SG measures how heavy the aggregate is compared to water; WA measures how much water fills the pores.\n\n3. Sieve Analysis — measures the particle size distribution (grading) of aggregate through a set of sieves.\n\n4. Material Finer than 75 Micron — measures the % of silt, clay, and dust particles washed away through a 75 micron sieve.\n\n5. Flakiness Index — measures the % of flat, thin (flaky) particles in coarse aggregate.\n\n6. Elongation Index — measures the % of long, stick-like (elongated) particles in coarse aggregate.\n\n7. Bulk Density — measures the weight of aggregate (including air voids between particles) per unit volume in kg/m³.\n\n8. Aggregate Crushing Value (ACV) — measures how much aggregate is crushed under a gradual load of 400 kN, expressed as % of fines generated.\n\nBonus: Aggregate Impact Value (AIV) — same sieve fraction as ACV, but measures resistance to sudden hammer blows (15 blows) instead of gradual loading."
